<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter xml:id="citing-this-guide">
  <title>Citing this Guide</title>
  <p>
    This suggested citation is:
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      <alert>Harrer, M., Cuijpers, P., Furukawa, T.A., &amp; Ebert, D.D.</alert> (2021). <em>Doing Meta-Analysis with R: A Hands-On Guide</em>. Boca Raton, FL and London: Chapman &amp; Hall/CRC Press. ISBN 978-0-367-61007-4.
    </p>
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    Download the citation as <url href="https://www.protectlab.org/meta-analysis-in-r/data/citation.bib">BibTeX</url> or <url href="https://www.protectlab.org/meta-analysis-in-r/data/citation.ris">RIS</url>. See <xref ref="references"/> for additional bibliographic files.
  </p>
  <p>
    The PreTeXt source format used for this edition is documented in <xref ref="pretext-guide"/>.
  </p>
</chapter>
